description._content: Catalog #: 15_000162 Title: Charles M. Daniels Collection Photo Aircraft/Subject: Focke-Wulf FW-190 F-8/R-1 Year Photo Taken: 1986 Daniels Album Name: Garber Facility, Smithsonian, '86 Notes From Album: Focke-Wulf FW-190 F-8, BMW 801D-2, 14 cylinder, 1700 hp (engine); Max speed: 402 mph @ 18,000 ft., Gross weight: 9,660 lbs. Additional Information: This aircraft was originally built as an A-7 fighter variant. After being damged in combet, the aircraft was rebuilt as a F-8 fighter bomber type. The Smithsonian received it in 1949. Restored to its original markings in the early 1980s. Repository: San Diego Air and Space Museum Archive
